FBIS4-48437 "drafr097_d_94016" FBIS-AFR-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Zambia Government Restores Opposition Party's Registration Government Restores Opposition Party's Registration MB1805191394 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network in English 1800 GMT 18 May 94 MB1805191394 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network English BFN [Text] The government has restored the certificate of registration of the United Democratic Party [UDP], which was disbanded after its president, Enock Kavindele, resigned. According to a letter signed by [name indistinct] and sent to [name indistinct] and company, the law firm which pursued the restoration of UDP, UDP has been advised to collect a certificate of registration. UDP Interim Party President Mr. Kapenda Okwuni released the letter to ZNBC [Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation] today. And Mr. Okwuni said now that the controversy over the existence of the party is over, the ward counselors in all councils where UDP has seats should continue to represent their electorate at council meetings.
